usergroups-createnew:
Dropdown option in [[Special:UserGroups]] to create a new user group.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Usergroups-editgroup-desc}}

usergroups-log-revoke:
Used as <code>$7</code> in the following message to specify if the newly created user group is a revoke-type, as defined by $wgRevokePermissions.
* {{msg-mw|Logentry-usergroups-create}}
{{Related|Usergroups-log-revoke}}

usergroups-log-revoke-switchon:
Used as <code>$7</code> in the following message to specify if the modified user group was switched to revoke type, as defined by $wgRevokePermissions.
* {{msg-mw|Logentry-usergroups-modify}}
{{Related|Usergroups-log-revoke}}

usergroups-log-revoke-switchoff:
Used as <code>$7</code> in the following message to specify if the modified user group was switched to normal type.
* {{msg-mw|Logentry-usergroups-modify}}
{{Related|Usergroups-log-revoke}}

invalidusergroupname-title:
Custom error title given when user enters invalid input into [[Special:UserGroups/new]].

The body for this title is:
* {{msg-mw|Invalidusergroupname-error}}

logentry-usergroups-create:
{{logentry}}
Additional parameters:
* $4 - user group name
* $5 - user rights
* $6 - (Unused)
* $7 - any one of the following:
** ''empty string''
** {{msg-mw|Usergroups-log-revoke}}
{{Related|Logentry-usergroups}}

logentry-usergroups-modify:
{{logentry}}
Additional parameters:
* $4 - user group name
* $5 - list of user rights added to the group, or {{msg-mw|Usergroups-log-none}}
* $6 - list of user rights removed from the group, or {{msg-mw|Usergroups-log-none}}
* $7 - any one of the following messages:
** ''empty string''
** {{msg-mw|Usergroups-log-revoke-switchon}}
** {{msg-mw|Usergroups-log-revoke-switchoff}}
{{Related|Logentry-usergroups}}
